  "text": "A unisolvent set of degrees of freedom of V h is given locally by that of 2D Hermite elements or 3D Argyris elements. Since the finite elements may have extra continuity on subsimplex, we briefly explain the implementation of the boundary conditions. Boundary condition of 2D Hermite FEM space. Since the first order derivatives are imposed on at vertices, for any v h ∈ V h , the tangential derivatives along the boundary should also be zero due to the consistency. In this case, we follow the terminology in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] to introduce the definition of corner vertices. At each corner boundary vertex, since the two tangential directions along the boundary form a basis of R 2 , we should impose both the first order derivatives to be zero. At a non-corner boundary vertex, the two tangential derivatives along its two adjacent edges coincide up to a sign. In this case, we only specify the degree of freedom value of this tangential derivative.",
